body:
This commit introduces a new lowering option to spill wires for expressions
with namehints. Previously, namehints are used only when they are
spilled to temporary wires but in terms of debuggability, it would
be good to have an option to probe expressions with namehints.
This commit also includes PrettifyVerilog change not to clone operations with namehints.

Example:
```mlir
 hw.module @namehint(%a: i5, %b: i5) -> (c: i5) {
    %0 = comb.add %a, %a {sv.namehint = "v1"} : i5
    %1 = comb.add %b, %0 {sv.namehint = "v2"} : i5
    hw.output %1 : i5
  }
```
`circt-opt -lowering-options=spillWiresForNamehints`
```verilog
module namehint(
  input  [4:0] a,
               b,
  output [4:0] c);

  wire [4:0] v2;
  wire [4:0] v1;

  assign v1 = a + a;
  assign v2 = b + v1;
  assign c = v2;
endmodule
```
